<subSubSection pageId="238" pageNumber="239" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="238.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="238" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,500,332,357]" pageId="238" pageNumber="239">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<collectingRegion box="[508,653,332,357]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="New Ireland" pageId="238" pageNumber="239">New Ireland</collectingRegion>
: 1, 2.—General distribution: South and East Africa, 
<collectingCountry box="[1252,1387,332,357]" name="Madagascar" pageId="238" pageNumber="239">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and Mascarenes east to 
<collectingCountry box="[380,443,367,392]" name="Wake Island" pageId="238" pageNumber="239">Wake</collectingCountry>
and Tuamotu islands, north to southern 
<collectingCountry box="[920,984,368,391]" name="Japan" pageId="238" pageNumber="239">Japan</collectingCountry>
and Ogasawara Islands, south to Lord Howe, Norfolk and Austral islands. Found in small groups on coral reefs, 
<quantity box="[981,1066,404,429]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="15.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="238" pageNumber="239" unit="m" value="7.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="0.0">0–15 m</quantity>
